    "body": "Follow up on #24648\nSplitting AITER Unified attention into its own backend class\nThe non-MLA selection logic on ROCm is now as follows:\n- The default is `TritonAttentionBackend`\n- If AITER is enabled together with VLLM_ROCM_USE_AITER_MHA, or ROCM_AITER_FA backend specified, use `AiterFlashAttentionBackend`\n- if AITER is enabled together with VLLM_ROCM_USE_AITER_UNIFIED_ATTENTION, or ROCM_AITER_UNIFIED_ATTN backend specified, use `RocmAiterUnifiedAttentionBackend`\n- if VLLM_V1_USE_PREFILL_DECODE_ATTENTION is set or ROCM_ATTN_VLLM_V1 is selected, use `RocmAttentionBackend`\n\nAdjusted attention fusion unit test to test all backends and removed v0 fusion test.\n",
